item.title: Swift VS Objective-C
item.description: What is the difference between Swift and Objective-C code after compilation? It will be very unfair comparison with simplest “Hello World” app. Swift Source code: import AppKit NSLog("Hello world") Compiler: $ swiftc --version Apple Swift version 5.1.3 (swiftlang-1100.0.282.1 clang-1100.0.33.15) Build: $ swiftc main.swift -o swift.out Compiled version of main function: push rbp mov rbp, rsp sub rsp, 30h xor eax, eax mov ecx, eax mov [rbp+var_4], edi mov rdi, rcx mov [rbp+var_10], rsi call Swift.
